name: alex singleton
text: Nice spot for tasty pizza. great location to chill, eat some good food. definitely worth going back to. this place has a good atmosphere.

name: Lynn Shaw
text: time and time again my pizza has been under cooked or absolutely burned. or half of my pizza is crust . So I give it another chance and again I'm let down. Sorry after the 6th chance I'm done. (Even after 2 times I've shown pictures to the manager )

name: Ashton Hickman
text: pizza and the feeling at this spot is great. super appetizing. the bill was appropriate for the quality.

name: Lee Locklear
text: Went to get 3 hot and ready pizzas. Only two available. I was told they don't keep them on the down times. Don't remember seeing that info in their advertisements.

name: USA Patriot
text: This location is now shut down. It was only a matter of time with the poor quality control and employees. The Domino's by Walmart is a much better option.

name: Stefanie M
text: Since the new manager took over costumer service has improved. I just had a great experience with the manager and staff.

name: Tracey Amburgey
text: The store was clean and food was yummy. Small town so may not have everything ready but happy to make anything you order.

name: Nick Haun
text: Can't answer the phone no customer service

name: Levi Shaw
text: I'm not a fan. I've seen the female manager work in the back in her pant and bra and then the other night 3 workers were out side smoking and on chick was popping zits on an dudes face.... we kept on and went to pizza hut. Edit/Update …More

name: Rebecca Cook
text: Asked the guy that claims to be the owner to put fresh wings in with the pizza I ordered, they didn't have what I wanted ready. I didn't mind waiting for the pizza, but he didn't want to put new wings in because there were wings …More

name: Denali Backcountry Guides
text: It's as good as any of it's peers. Cheap, fast and friendly, but not the highest quality cheese.

name: jane crone
text:
I am sorry but my carry out large Vegetable pizza last night was a disappointment... cardboard crust. did not appear to have been made in house
Lacked any flavor
Probably will go elsewhere.

name: Douglas Towing
text: Like the pizza BUT I have never walked in and ordered and not had to wait even when they are not busy. Thought it was supposed to be fast not in fbg. But I still eat there.

name: Susan Maddison
text: I always get bread sticks and I always have to wait.  I usually call ahead and sometimes have to wait then too but it's faster and cheaper than Dominos.  The pizza is really good for the price!!

name: Willow Mist Farm
text: Good location in town. Deliveries are quick. Pizza eas fresh and gave a 8 dollar tip

name: Mike Pippen
text: Love their marinara sauce

name: Mandy M
text: Corporate shut the Fredericksburg location down. It is no longer there.

name: alisha contreras
text: Worst customer service ! They think playing games on the phone instead of taking an order and then insulting their customers is what they are paid to do . Asinine at best .

name: Miguel Mondragon
text: Don't show up close to closing time cooks get extremely mad if you do

name: Wayne Windham
text: Never have any crazy bread and barely have pizza.

name: Karen Jamison
text: Quick efficient service.

name: James Payne
text: Showed up at 8:30. Sign said open until 10:00.  Doors were locked and employees inside were yelling they were closed.

name: Jesus Perez
text: This place has closed down recently

name: Gary Poffenbarger
text: Cheep and fast

name: Debbie Reed
text: I like the pizza they make and they cost less

name: Gil Camacho
text: Bad service.
